{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.29",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 29,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 29",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 29 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:1",
      "text": "And Job again took up his discourse, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:2",
      "text": "“Oh, that I were as in the months of old, as in the days when God watched over me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:3",
      "text": "when his lamp shone upon my head, and by his light I walked through darkness;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:4",
      "text": "as I was in my autumn days, when the friendship of God was upon my tent;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:5",
      "text": "when the Almighty was yet with me, when my children were about me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:6",
      "text": "when my steps were washed with milk, and the rock poured out for me streams of oil!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:7",
      "text": "When I went out to the gate of the city, when I prepared my seat in the square,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:8",
      "text": "the young men saw me and withdrew, and the aged rose and stood;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:9",
      "text": "the princes refrained from talking, and laid their hand on their mouth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:10",
      "text": "the voice of the nobles was hushed, and their tongue cleaved to the roof of their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:11",
      "text": "When the ear heard, it called me blessed, and when the eye saw, it approved;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:12",
      "text": "because I delivered the poor who cried, and the fatherless who had none to help him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:13",
      "text": "The blessing of him who was about to perish came upon me, and I caused the widow's heart to sing for joy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:14",
      "text": "I put on righteousness, and it clothed me; my justice was like a robe and a turban.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:15",
      "text": "I was eyes to the blind, and feet to the lame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:16",
      "text": "I was a father to the poor, and I searched out the cause of him whom I did not know.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:17",
      "text": "I broke the fangs of the unrighteous, and made him drop his prey from his teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:18",
      "text": "Then I thought, ‘I shall die in my nest, and I shall multiply my days as the sand,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:19",
      "text": "my roots spread out to the waters, with the dew all night on my branches,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:20",
      "text": "my glory fresh with me, and my bow ever new in my hand.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:21",
      "text": "“Men listened to me, and waited, and kept silence for my counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:22",
      "text": "After I spoke they did not speak again, and my word dropped upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:23",
      "text": "They waited for me as for the rain; and they opened their mouths as for the spring rain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:24",
      "text": "I smiled on them when they had no confidence; and the light of my countenance they did not cast down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.29.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:25",
      "text": "I chose their way, and sat as chief, and I dwelt like a king among his troops, like one who comforts mourners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
